rdf:Description.lla:note: The Maiden Bower registered at the port of Scilly.

There is an account in the Official Log, regarding the death of Thomas Griffiths and William Meyrick. The pair were 'spreading the after awning, when William Mayrick fell over board off the sail'. The Master states how he threw a life buoy out for him, but that he had drifted too far. He then states that in the meantime Thomas Griffiths 'jumped over board and swam after him and succeeded on getting hold of him when he grasped Griffiths by the arms and both suddenly disappeared and never came to the surface anymore'. The Master states that the 'boat was manned instantly... but to no avail'.
